text: Ishtybayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Bolsheshadinsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 295 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 13 km from Mishkino, 6 km from Bolshiye Shady. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Ishtybayevo
